### Fix 4: Enable Thinking for Complex Chat Questions

**File:** `packages/agent-runtime/src/companyAgentRunner.ts`

Currently thinking is blanket-disabled for on_demand. This should be conditional:

```typescript
// Current:
// on_demand: thinking DISABLED (speed)

// New: 
// on_demand: thinking ENABLED for complex questions, DISABLED for simple ones
//
// Complexity heuristic (cheap — no model call):
const isComplex = (message: string): boolean => {
  // Long messages are usually complex
  if (message.length > 200) return true;
  // Questions with multiple parts
  if ((message.match(/\?/g) || []).length > 1) return true;
  // Comparison/analysis keywords
  if (/\b(compare|analyze|evaluate|recommend|strategy|should we|trade-?off|pros and cons)\b/i.test(message)) return true;
  // References to previous context
  if (/\b(you said|you mentioned|earlier|yesterday|last time|follow up|what about)\b/i.test(message)) return true;
  return false;
};

// In model call setup:
const thinkingEnabled = task !== 'on_demand' || isComplex(message);
```

This adds ~1-2s latency for complex questions but dramatically improves answer quality.
Simple questions ("How's the platform?", "What's our MRR?") stay fast.

